TECHNICAL ASSESSMENT
Four data collection approaches were tested. Here's the honest report on each.
✓ Web search
Highly effective. Used to triangulate expert credibility, verify claims, and find actual LinkedIn posts and conference talks. Returned real 2025–26 content.
	~ YouTube transcripts
Supadata API exists and is production-ready (100 free req/mo.). YouTube.com blocked direct fetch (429). Supadata requires API key signup   feasible in a live environment, not inside a sandboxed demo.

✓ Web fetch
Partially effective. Fetched actual LinkedIn post content, Substack articles, and conference talk transcripts where publicly indexed.
	~ LinkedIn scraping
LinkedIn blocks unauthenticated scraping. Post snippets surfaced via Google indexing   adequate for sampling recent themes, not full post text. Manual collection is the reliable path.




